	   <tr><td colspan=2>Zuranthium,<br><br>Your posts by and large are quite informative.&nbsp;&nbsp;I learned a great deal about the Magician Class from them.  Nothing that I hadn't ALREADY learned, from other sites, but still informative.<br><br>However, all the good guides in the world don't justify your attitude towards other posters.  In my efforts to learn more about the Magician, I've been flipping through this board, and I found some things that I think the other posters here will find interesting.<br><br>Your guide is posted at least twice here, the VERY long one.  Once under its own thread, and once in someone else's thread, about their own guide.  To me, in a clear effort to try to shut out anybody else's guide but your own.<br><br>On several occasions, you posted responses to other people's guides.  In just about every one of those replies, you disagreed very rudely with the people who wrote those guides, basically calling their opinions stupid and idiotic.  Then you would occasionaly call yourself a 'Master Magician', tell them to stop acting like they know more than you, and reference them to your own guide.<br><br>As to your 'Master Magician' status.  I recall a post where someone informed the board that you're really a Magician in your lower twenties.  Could you please, for the basis of accurately evaluating your guides, post your specific level so people will know?<br><br>All of that is for the other posters here.  I want anyone who is considering posting a guide, to be welcome to do so.  I promise them, no matter what this Zuranthium may threaten, you will have readers.<br><br>For myself, Zuranthium, I am extremely irritated by your very arrogant attitude and condescension towards other posters.  IMO, Centhat was right on the money earlier, and he owed you no apologies.  I am not going to read ANY of your posts or guides until you decide to stop lambasting anyone who tries to compete with your guides.  This isn't your board.  Stop your silly power play.  Apologize in a seperate post for your repeated insults and arrogance.  Also, stop plagiarizing other guides.  When you wrote your guide, you should have SPECIFICALLY cited the other guides used.  You did not.  You led others to believe that your guide was the fruits of your brain alone. It was not.<br><br>Werokh Mormegil/Amandil &lt;Akh Valahr&gt;<br>Dwarven Paladin/High Elf Magician<br>Cazic-Thule Server<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
