	   <tr><td colspan=2>Calm down, it's a game.&nbsp;&nbsp;I've have read in many places that humans do get exp bonus.  I'd have to look for the sources now, but others can read eqcasters, stratics, everlore, and find the same references.<br><br>I don't want to be rude to you, but I have a different opinion than you on races.  Gnome and High-elves do get night vision.  That's great! If that is a concern for people, then they should play those races.  The point of my note was to say play the race you like best and equalize out the stats with equipment or equipment that enhances your short comings (like night vision).<br><br>I prefer the Euridite for his starting INT.  It is the primary stat and I like not having to look as much of INT equipment. Also for trade skills I like having the high INT early on so that you can get the skills up before you get INT equipment. I quickly moved him to Qeynos and got a bind there.  I agree that there are good spots in Feydwer. I also feel that Qeynos and Freeport are good spots as well.  There are a great number of mobs in the newbie area and good adjacent areas to move to.  I had a lot of fun in BB. Trains were bad but there are some great places in the dungeon that are fairly low risk and give great exp because few people move to those areas.<br><br>I've always thought of a high elf more for the WIS. In the end, once you get beyond the Euridite the other races (except human) are all pretty close on INT. So, again, if you want the night vision, then play the high elf and look for equipment to make up the INT.<br><br>Zuranthium, these boards are for everyone to express their opinions, not just you. I don't appreciate you personal attack.  I never said I knew more, just that my opinon is different.  As you get older you will learn that part of life, and your success, is how you handle other people with views that may not be the same as yours. I too have written articles on specific issues (managing magician engagement risk, solo hunting strategy, and a new article to be published soon)which have been published on the stratics website. While I may not be a master magician, I am not a newbie to the game and have put some thought into how to play it.  I'm interested in, and respect your opinions, I would ask that you give the same respect to myself and others that post on these boards.<br><br>Cetus<br>The Nameless<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
